<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?> 
<crossway-bible>
	<book title="Luke" num="41">
		<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006001">
		</marker>
		<chapter num="6">
			<heading
				>
				Jesus Is Lord of the Sabbath
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="1">
				<crossref let="s" cid="c42006001.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t42006001.1">
				</crossref>
				On a Sabbath,
				<note nid="n42006001.1">
				</note>
				 while he was going through the grainfields, his disciples 
				<crossref let="t" cid="c42006001.2">
				</crossref>
				plucked and ate some heads of grain, rubbing them in their hands.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006002">
			</marker>
			<verse num="2">
				But some of the Pharisees said, 
				<crossref let="u" cid="c42006002.1">
				</crossref>
				<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
				Why are you doing 
				<crossref let="v" cid="c42006002.2">
				</crossref>
				what is not lawful to do on the Sabbath?
				<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
				</q>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006003">
			</marker>
			<verse num="3">
				And Jesus answered them, 
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="w" cid="c42006003.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Have you not read 
					<crossref let="x" cid="c42006003.2">
					</crossref>
					what David did when he was hungry, he and those who were with him:
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006004">
			</marker>
			<verse num="4" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					how he entered the house of God and took and ate 
					<crossref let="y" cid="c42006004.1">
					</crossref>
					the bread of the Presence, 
					<crossref let="y" cid="c42006004.2">
					</crossref>
					which is not lawful for any but the priests to eat, and also gave it to those with him?
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006005">
			</marker>
			<verse num="5">
				And he said to them, 
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="z" cid="c42006005.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					The Son of Man is lord of the Sabbath.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006006">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				A Man with a Withered Hand
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="6">
				On another Sabbath, 
				<crossref let="a" cid="c42006006.1">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t42006006.1">
				</crossref>
				he entered the synagogue 
				<crossref let="b" cid="c42006006.2">
				</crossref>
				and was teaching, and a man was there whose right hand was withered.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006007">
			</marker>
			<verse num="7">
				And the scribes and the Pharisees 
				<crossref let="c" cid="c42006007.1">
				</crossref>
				watched him, to see whether he would heal on the Sabbath, 
				<crossref let="d" cid="c42006007.2">
				</crossref>
				so that they might find a reason to accuse him.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006008">
			</marker>
			<verse num="8">
				But 
				<crossref let="e" cid="c42006008.1">
				</crossref>
				he knew their thoughts, and he said to the man with the withered hand, 
				<woc
					>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Come and stand here.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
				 And he rose and stood there.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006009">
			</marker>
			<verse num="9">
				And Jesus said to them, 
				<woc
					>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					I ask you, 
					<crossref let="f" cid="c42006009.1">
					</crossref>
					is it lawful on the Sabbath to do good or to do harm, to save life or to destroy it?
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006010">
			</marker>
			<verse num="10">
				And 
				<crossref let="g" cid="c42006010.1">
				</crossref>
				after looking around at them all he said to him, 
				<woc
					>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Stretch out your hand.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
				 And 
				<crossref let="h" cid="c42006010.2">
				</crossref>
				he did so, and his hand was restored.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006011">
			</marker>
			<verse num="11">
				But they were filled with 
				<crossref let="i" cid="c42006011.1">
				</crossref>
				fury and discussed with one another what they might do to Jesus.
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006012">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				The Twelve Apostles
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="12">
				In these days 
				<crossref let="j" cid="c42006012.1">
				</crossref>
				he went out to the mountain to pray, and all night he continued in prayer to God.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006013">
			</marker>
			<verse num="13">
				And when day came, 
				<crossref let="k" cid="c42006013.1">
				</crossref>
				he called his disciples 
				<crossref let="l" cid="c42006013.2">
				</crossref>
				<crossref cid="t42006013.1">
				</crossref>
				and 
				<crossref let="m" cid="c42006013.3">
				</crossref>
				chose from them twelve, whom he named 
				<crossref let="n" cid="c42006013.4">
				</crossref>
				apostles:
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006014">
			</marker>
			<verse num="14">
				Simon, 
				<crossref let="o" cid="c42006014.1">
				</crossref>
				whom he named Peter, and 
				<crossref let="p" cid="c42006014.2">
				</crossref>
				Andrew his brother, and 
				<crossref let="p" cid="c42006014.3">
				</crossref>
				James and John, and Philip, and Bartholomew,
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006015">
			</marker>
			<verse num="15">
				and 
				<crossref let="q" cid="c42006015.1">
				</crossref>
				Matthew, and Thomas, and James the son of Alphaeus, and Simon who was called 
				<crossref let="r" cid="c42006015.2">
				</crossref>
				the Zealot,
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006016">
			</marker>
			<verse num="16">
				and 
				<crossref let="s" cid="c42006016.1">
				</crossref>
				Judas the son of James, and Judas Iscariot, who became a traitor.
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006017">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				Jesus Ministers to a Great Multitude
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="17">
				And 
				<crossref let="t" cid="c42006017.1">
				</crossref>
				he came down with them and stood on a level place, with 
				<crossref let="u" cid="c42006017.2">
				</crossref>
				a great crowd of his disciples and a great multitude of people from all Judea and Jerusalem and the seacoast of 
				<crossref let="v" cid="c42006017.3">
				</crossref>
				Tyre and Sidon,
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006018">
			</marker>
			<verse num="18">
				who came to hear him and to be healed of their diseases. 
				<crossref let="w" cid="c42006018.1">
				</crossref>
				And those who were troubled with unclean spirits were cured.
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006019">
			</marker>
			<verse num="19">
				And all the crowd 
				<crossref let="x" cid="c42006019.1">
				</crossref>
				sought to touch him, for 
				<crossref let="y" cid="c42006019.2">
				</crossref>
				power came out from him and healed them all.
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006020">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				The Beatitudes
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="20">
				And 
				<crossref let="z" cid="c42006020.1">
				</crossref>
				he lifted up his eyes on his disciples, 
				<crossref let="a" cid="c42006020.2">
				</crossref>
				and said:

				<end-paragraph
					>
				</end-paragraph>
				<begin-paragraph
					>
				</begin-paragraph>
				<woc
					>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Blessed are you who are poor, for 
					<crossref let="b" cid="c42006020.3">
					</crossref>
					yours is the kingdom of God.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006021">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="21" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="c" cid="c42006021.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Blessed are you who are hungry now, for you shall be satisfied.
				</woc>
				<end-paragraph
					>
				</end-paragraph>
				<begin-paragraph
					>
				</begin-paragraph>
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="d" cid="c42006021.2">
					</crossref>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Blessed are you who weep now, for you shall laugh.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006022">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="22" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Blessed are you when 
					<crossref let="e" cid="c42006022.1">
					</crossref>
					people hate you and when they 
					<crossref let="f" cid="c42006022.2">
					</crossref>
					exclude you and revile you and 
					<crossref let="g" cid="c42006022.3">
					</crossref>
					spurn your name as evil, 
					<crossref let="h" cid="c42006022.4">
					</crossref>
					on account of the Son of Man!
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006023">
			</marker>
			<verse num="23" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="i" cid="c42006023.1">
					</crossref>
					Rejoice in that day, and leap for joy, for behold, your reward is great in heaven; for 
					<crossref let="j" cid="c42006023.2">
					</crossref>
					so their fathers did to the prophets.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006024">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				Jesus Pronounces Woes
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="24" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="k" cid="c42006024.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					But woe to you who are rich, 
					<crossref let="l" cid="c42006024.2">
					</crossref>
					for you 
					<crossref let="m" cid="c42006024.3">
					</crossref>
					have received your consolation.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006025">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="25" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Woe to you who are full now, for 
					<crossref let="n" cid="c42006025.1">
					</crossref>
					you shall be hungry.
				</woc>
				<end-paragraph
					>
				</end-paragraph>
				<begin-paragraph
					>
				</begin-paragraph>
				<woc
					>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Woe to 
					<crossref let="o" cid="c42006025.2">
					</crossref>
					you who laugh now, 
					<crossref let="o" cid="c42006025.3">
					</crossref>
					for you shall mourn and weep.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006026">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="26" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Woe to you, 
					<crossref let="p" cid="c42006026.1">
					</crossref>
					when all people speak well of you, for 
					<crossref let="q" cid="c42006026.2">
					</crossref>
					so their fathers did to 
					<crossref let="r" cid="c42006026.3">
					</crossref>
					the false prophets.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006027">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				Love Your Enemies
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="27" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					But I say to you who hear, 
					<crossref let="s" cid="c42006027.1">
					</crossref>
					Love your enemies, 
					<crossref let="t" cid="c42006027.2">
					</crossref>
					do good to those who hate you,
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006028">
			</marker>
			<verse num="28" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="u" cid="c42006028.1">
					</crossref>
					bless those who curse you, 
					<crossref let="s" cid="c42006028.2">
					</crossref>
					pray for those who abuse you.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006029">
			</marker>
			<verse num="29" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="v" cid="c42006029.1">
					</crossref>
					<crossref cid="t42006029.1">
					</crossref>
					To one who 
					<crossref let="w" cid="c42006029.2">
					</crossref>
					strikes you on the cheek, offer the other also, and from one who takes away your cloak do not withhold your tunic
					<note nid="n42006029.1">
					</note>
					 either.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006030">
			</marker>
			<verse num="30" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="x" cid="c42006030.1">
					</crossref>
					Give to everyone who begs from you, and from one who takes away your goods do not demand them back.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006031">
			</marker>
			<verse num="31" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					And 
					<crossref let="y" cid="c42006031.1">
					</crossref>
					as you wish that others would do to you, do so to them.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006032">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="32" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="z" cid="c42006032.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					If you love those who love you, what benefit is that to you? For even sinners love those who love them.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006033">
			</marker>
			<verse num="33" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					And if you do good to those who do good to you, what benefit is that to you? For even sinners do the same.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006034">
			</marker>
			<verse num="34" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					And 
					<crossref let="a" cid="c42006034.1">
					</crossref>
					if you 
					<crossref let="b" cid="c42006034.2">
					</crossref>
					lend to those from whom you expect to receive, what credit is that to you? Even sinners lend to sinners, to get back the same amount.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006035">
			</marker>
			<verse num="35" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					But 
					<crossref let="c" cid="c42006035.1">
					</crossref>
					love your enemies, and do good, and lend, expecting nothing in return, and your reward will be great, and 
					<crossref let="d" cid="c42006035.2">
					</crossref>
					you will be sons of 
					<crossref let="e" cid="c42006035.3">
					</crossref>
					the Most High, for 
					<crossref let="f" cid="c42006035.4">
					</crossref>
					he is kind to the ungrateful and the evil.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006036">
			</marker>
			<verse num="36" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="g" cid="c42006036.1">
					</crossref>
					Be merciful, even as 
					<crossref let="h" cid="c42006036.2">
					</crossref>
					your Father is merciful.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006037">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				Judging Others
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="37" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossrefs
						>
						<crossref let="i" cid="c42006037.1">
						</crossref>
						<crossref let="j" cid="c42006037.2">
						</crossref>
					</crossrefs>
					<crossref cid="t42006037.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Judge not, and you will not be judged; condemn not, and you will not be condemned; 
					<crossref let="j" cid="c42006037.3">
					</crossref>
					forgive, and you will be forgiven;
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006038">
			</marker>
			<verse num="38" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="k" cid="c42006038.1">
					</crossref>
					give, and it will be given to you. Good measure, pressed down, shaken together, running over, will be put 
					<crossref let="l" cid="c42006038.2">
					</crossref>
					into your lap. For 
					<crossref let="m" cid="c42006038.3">
					</crossref>
					with the measure you use it will be measured back to you.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006039">
			</marker>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="39">
				He also told them a parable: 
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="n" cid="c42006039.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="begin-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Can a blind man lead a blind man? Will they not both fall into a pit?
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006040">
			</marker>
			<verse num="40" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="o" cid="c42006040.1">
					</crossref>
					A disciple is not above his teacher, but everyone when he is 
					<crossref let="p" cid="c42006040.2">
					</crossref>
					fully trained will be like his teacher.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006041">
			</marker>
			<verse num="41" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="i" cid="c42006041.1">
					</crossref>
					Why do you see the speck that is in your brother's eye, but 
					<crossref let="q" cid="c42006041.2">
					</crossref>
					do not notice the log that is in your own eye?
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006042">
			</marker>
			<verse num="42" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					How can you say to your brother, 
					<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Brother, let me take out the speck that is in your eye,
					<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					 when you yourself do not see the log that is in your own eye? You hypocrite, first take the log out of your own eye, and then you will see clearly to take out the speck that is in your brother's eye.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006043">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				A Tree and Its Fruit
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="43" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					For 
					<crossref let="r" cid="c42006043.1">
					</crossref>
					<crossref cid="t42006043.1">
					</crossref>
					no good tree bears bad fruit, nor again does a bad tree bear good fruit,
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006044">
			</marker>
			<verse num="44" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					for 
					<crossref let="s" cid="c42006044.1">
					</crossref>
					each tree is known by its own fruit. For figs are not gathered from thornbushes, nor are grapes picked from a bramble bush.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006045">
			</marker>
			<verse num="45" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="t" cid="c42006045.1">
					</crossref>
					The good person out of the good treasure of his heart produces good, and the evil person out of his evil treasure produces 
					<crossref let="u" cid="c42006045.2">
					</crossref>
					evil, 
					<crossref let="v" cid="c42006045.3">
					</crossref>
					for out of the abundance of the heart his mouth speaks.
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006046">
			</marker>
			<heading
				>
				Build Your House on the Rock
			</heading>
			<begin-paragraph
				>
			</begin-paragraph>
			<verse num="46" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="w" cid="c42006046.1">
					</crossref>
					<q class="continue-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Why 
					<crossref let="x" cid="c42006046.2">
					</crossref>
					do you call me 
					<q class="begin-single" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					Lord, Lord,
					<q class="end-single" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
					 and not do what I tell you?
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006047">
			</marker>
			<verse num="47" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="y" cid="c42006047.1">
					</crossref>
					<crossref cid="t42006047.1">
					</crossref>
					Everyone who comes to me and hears my words and does them, I will show you what he is like:
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006048">
			</marker>
			<verse num="48" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					he is like a man building a house, who dug deep and laid the foundation on the rock. And when a flood arose, the stream broke against that house and could not shake it, because it had been well built.
					<note nid="n42006048.1">
					</note>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<marker class="begin-verse" mid="v42006049">
			</marker>
			<verse num="49" class="woc">
				<woc
					>
					<crossref let="z" cid="c42006049.1">
					</crossref>
					But the one who hears and does not do them is like a man who built a house on the ground without a foundation. When the stream broke against it, immediately it fell, and 
					<crossref let="a" cid="c42006049.2">
					</crossref>
					the ruin of that house was great.
					<q class="end-double" qid="" from="" to="">
					</q>
				</woc>
			</verse>
			<end-paragraph
				>
			</end-paragraph>
		</chapter>
	</book>
</crossway-bible>


